The paper deals with the algorithmic problem of testing whether a given abstract graph is an intersection graph of segments, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also introduces and discusses the class of computational problems denoted by $\exists\mathbb{R}$, which involves solving systems of polynomial inequalities over the reals, and the paper establishes $\exists\mathbb{R}$-completeness of several problems, which falls under the categories of algorithms and complexity (cs.DS, cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also presents a decision algorithm for the first-order theory of the reals, which is related to logic and foundations of mathematics (cs.LO).
